{{Politics of Tunisia}}
[[File:Ministere education tun.JPG|thumb|The Ministry of Education building]]
The '''Ministry of Education''' is responsible for the administration of education in Tunisia. It has its headquarters at Boulevard Bab Bnet 1030 in [[Tunis]]. As of 2015 it was directed by [[Néji Jalloul]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.leaders.com.tn/article/17005-lettre-ouverte-a-mr-neji-jalloul-ministre-de-l-education|title=Lettre ouverte à Mr. Néji Jalloul, ministre de l’Education|publisher=Leaders.com.tn|accessdate=7 June 2015|language=French}}</ref>In May 2017, the government sacked Jalloul from his position, to appoint Slim Khalbous instead.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.africanews.com/2017/05/01/tunisia-ministers-of-finance-and-education-sacked/|title=Tunisia: Ministers of finance and education sacked|last=AfricaNews|date=2017-05-03|website=Africanews|access-date=2017-05-03}}</ref>

The department is responsible for ensuring the right to education and training of all Tunisians according to law No. 2002-80 of 23 July 2002 on education.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ibe.unesco.org/National_Reports/ICE_2004/tunisia_fr.pdf|title=RAPPORT NATIONAL SUR LE DEVELOPPEMENT DE L'EDUCATION 2000-2004|publisher=UNESCO|accessdate=7 June 2015|language=French}}</ref> It pays special attention to children with special needs and those of Tunisian nationals abroad. The department facilitates public education and training systems and institutions and structures on a local, regional and national scale, and also overlooks private schools and preschooling.

